&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt?&gt;Warrior &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. Aggro:&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;A. Taunt success Rate, particularly against even con mobs and higher is abysmal. We understand that there is a fix in the works, can we get an estimated time? Also, can we get a notification that it's on test that we may perform the necessary testing to ensure that it's appropriate prior to going live?&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;B. Taunt Greying out on Out of Range: This has been said to have been something which was supposed to be being fixed, when is this going to happen?&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;C. Initial aggro limitations: This is becoming a serious issue for warriors See the following for more detailed information.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Paladin generated hate from spells&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;1800 (1 sec cast, 12 sec recast) 100m (Ancient force of jeron)&lt;BR&gt;1400 (2 sec cast, 24 sec recast) 250m (Serene command)&lt;BR&gt;1600 (1 sec cast, 12 sec recast) 80m (Force of Piety)&lt;BR&gt;1200(est) (1.5 sec cast, 9 sec recast) 15m (Cease)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In 30 seconds, one could cast.... intentially low estimates, a good Paladin could cast at least 1 more of each of the force spells.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;2x Ancient force&lt;BR&gt;2x Force of piety&lt;BR&gt;1x Serene command&lt;BR&gt;2x Cease&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;For a total of: 10600 hate in casts only for 640 mana.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Shadowknight hate generated from spells&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;A SK can cast &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;1800AE, no Mez Break (3 sec cast, 30 sec recast) 150m (Dread Gaze)&lt;BR&gt;1800 Hate (1.5 sec cast, 6 sec recast) 60m (Terror of discord)&lt;BR&gt;Whole series of other spells such as clinging darkness, etc &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;3x Terror of Discord&lt;BR&gt;1x Dread Gaze&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Total of 7200 hate for 330 mana (not counting misc hate generating spells, which can easily be added in as necessary)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Warrior generated hate:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;600 (+100/tick for 10 ticks, instant) 350END (Bazu bellow)&lt;BR&gt;1000AE + Melee damage (instant, limitations on use due to mez breaking) 605 END (Cyclone Blade)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Total of 2100 hate for 955 END&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The default is 1100 hate total, 600 in initial chunk for 305 END, and cyclone if needed, lately it's usually needed.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;It's one thing to have 1/5th to 1/10th of the aggro potential of your competitors for groups, it's entirely another to have it at such a high cost for the resource used, and have the resource used regenerate at a lower rate than the competitor's. It's kind of a "triple penalty", and furthermore, after the initial part is used up, we're "stuck", and cannot compensate at all in the event of a catastrophic aggro loss, especially in the condition taunt is in. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;While one can advise aggro management, it's simply not fair for such "aggro management" to only need to be applied to only one of the 3 tank classes, or for the spread in the ability to generate hate to be so far apart. The tanking advantage is nowhere near that in favor of warriors. The aggro disadvantage should be inverse to the tanking advantage.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;This is further compounded with the advent of Touch of Draygun, and the proliferation of Echo of Anger 4 belts for all 3 classes, which brought Paladins and SK's up to warriors' modified levels, when they already had an enormous lead on warriors in initial aggro. Widening the gap in initial aggro is not a desirable thing, but that's been happenning lately to a degree that puts warriors at a tremendous disadvantage. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The other aggro issue is stagnation in weaponry, but that will be covered under the weaponry entry in the top 10 list.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;2. Endurance Regen: We need endurance regen from Spells and/or items. Modrods should provide an endurance benefit equal to the mana benefit. Also, change + Endurance only augments to +Endurance regen. Particularly crucial in this is post-resurrection/looting endurance regen. &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be&amp;nbsp;considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Additional Notes: With the current aggro stagnation warriors have had, we use cyclone blade more and more often lately on single targets, which really drains our endurance in single groups. The endurance costs along with the downtime involved in regenerating the endurance, makes us the least effective tank when it comes to constant killing. Please address endurance costs for aggro skills.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;3. Re-Evaluate warrior disciplines. &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be&amp;nbsp;considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There's a few issues: &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;A. Endurance costs on all of the new discs is WAY too high (Part of the proposed first pass with class re-envisioning posted on EQLive on 3/14/2005)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;B. Aura of Runes negates the use of inherent proc right clicks. Please consider "suspending" them rather than dispelling them completely. Furthermore, the rate of fire is too low for it to be worth the endurance spent. Also, please unlink from healing will. being penalized in downtime for invoking something which allows you to survive a fight shouldn't happen.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;C. The level 70 discipline needs to be effective against even con and higher mobs. If it's not reasonable to make level 70+ mobs stunnable (and it's probably not reasonable), then change the effect to a dramatic defensive based damage shield (DD) effect, or a "defensive" hate inducing proc, or something along those lines. As it currently stands, there's not a whole lot of use for the discipline which SHOULD be our best. If, as part of the "re-envisioning", stuns work on targets even level or higher, then it needs to fire a LOT more often than it does in order to be useful.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;D. Savage onslaught needs a longer timer or shorter refresh and a MUCH lower endurance upkeep.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Update: Please let us know if the "Cleave" effect is working with Savage Onslaught.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;4. Warriors need to be distinguished in durability in single group content from knights (and by extension, other classes).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;!-- / message --&gt;&lt;!-- sig --&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;This has gotten a little better in Depths, but the issue of crit heal AA's working with Reptile skin giving knights (at least Paladins) another advantage when grouping with druids, aside from the complimentary buffset.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;5. Shields: Please give warriors a reason to use a shield. Either in "one handed" non dual wielding weapons, or a modifier to one handed weapon damage when a shield is equipped, warriors don't like having a 5% "mitigation' advantage while giving up a 5% avoidance advantage to classes who can contribute in their own survivability, simply because only one class is rendered impotent while using a shield, and the other two aren't.&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;!-- / message --&gt;&lt;!-- sig --&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;6. Availability of weapons upgrades across the board: &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;A. Non-raiding warriors are really suffering from a lack of viable upgrades that aren't inferior to older weapon choices. Particularly true is the dilemma that warriors in groups are essentially using the same weapons as other dual wielding DPS classes, and there's nothing that's really warrior oriented in single group acquirable weaponry that's current. There really needs to be some movement in weaponry. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;B. Raiding warriors have been waiting some 4 expansions for an upgrade to the Brutish Blade of Balance, or an offhandable warrior oriented weapon. The issue is that we're seeing is that we're being viewed as a generic dual wielding DPS class, and we're not. We're a tank class with needs that differ from rangers, rogues, monks, beastlords, and bards. We have defensive and aggro needs that supercede our offensive needs. Each "upgrade" to the Brutish Blade isn't really an upgrade at all. It's more of an upgrade in one of three areas. For instance, the Notched Blade of Bloodletting is a DPS upgrade, the proc is a downgrade, and the defensive stats are a large downgrade from the brutish blade. The same is true of the only other real alternative, Swiftcleave. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Warriors do not feel it's appropriate to put "warrior" on regular DPS weapons and consider us "itemized for". If there's daggers with Backstab mods, Bows with Archery mods, weapons with instrument mods, there should be something that makes a warrior "the desired" class if a warrior only weapon isn't a viable option (and we do not see why it isn't a viable option).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;7. Mob Summonning Issues: Please make it so that mobs summon rather than in the exact center of their hitbox, in front of them. Being summonned "out of melee range" and turning the mobs all over the place is incredibly frustrating, or better yet make mobs who have been attempted to have been taunted in the last 10 seconds stop summonning. The concept that we're standing in the face of a mob attacking and taunting should be clear indication that we're not trying "to evade" the mobs. &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;8. Downward Scaling Tool: There is a point in EQ where because of the nature of certain spells (Stuns, Tap AA's), warriors take a back seat to Knights of their level at taking melee damage. In order to remain competitive, warriors need a low end, downward scaling tool which relives this. All of warriors' current tools become more effective the harder the content, but we lack a tool which has strength in weaker content. &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;9. Warriors have been historically an "anti-magic" class, we would like some more innate magical defenses than simply a few points of MR. At higher levels, especially with the vet AA infusion, this is not a meaningful addition. Things we would like to see are things like innate spellshield of 10% to magic based spells at level 70, innate dispel resistance chance, a higher than cap magic resist and other such anti-magic resistances, even via class only AA. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Warrior gear is quite short on spellshield mods and surprisingly, magic resist, and we'd like to have our innate magic resistance mean something.&amp;nbsp; &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR&gt;10. Augments: The addition of vendor based DoN proc augments was great, but there's still a lack of dropped augments, or upgraded effect augments from dropped mobs. This was supposed to have been added in DoN, but none have been found yet. We'd like to see a greater range of dropped hate generating augments.&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;One further thing on augments. With the proliferation of all/all enraging blow augments and chaotic strike augments, and people who use them, the "advantage" to warrior specific aggro augments has decreased steadily, leading back to the old aggro issue. Warriors need some specific warrior only aggro augments which are qualitatively better than others can have access to. &lt;!-- / message --&gt;&lt;!-- sig --&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
