&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;8. Soloing: Being able to solo isn't just being able to endure the beating of a single target at a time, but rather lots of other stuff, such as being able to get to the area where experience happens, being able to engage a single mob, being able to have a contingency plan to deal with adds, being able to have en escape mechanism when things go awry, also there's the matter of downtime between kills. Warriors are extremely weak in all of these areas, not just "one mob DPS vs. one warrior DPS", and any reasonable soloing needs to take these factors into account, not just 'how to make one mob able to be killed by one warrior".&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; (currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
